<TITLE> Forex reserves new high, lending rate may fall: BB </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 9 (bdnews24.com)The foreign currency reserve has topped $8 billion in the first month of new FY 2009-10, a new high, on remittance flow, the central bank chief said on Sunday. The interest rate on lending may come down on the healthy reserve, Bangladesh Bank governor Atiur Rahman hinted at an annual conference of state-owned commercial bank Janata Bank Limited held at BIAM auditorium in Dhaka. According to BB data, a total of $9.63 billion came in in the FY 2008-2009. "We want to use the reserve in domestic investment. The exporters can take loans from the reserve. It might help reduce the rate of interest. "We are mulling over allowing the exporters to provide loans from the reserve," Rahman added. "The exporters will get loan in foreign currency from the reserve fund. As they earn foreign exchange after export they can pay back the loan in foreign currency, making the whole thing a 'win-win situation' for both parties," the governor explained. He asked the banks to take steps to invest Tk 7,500 crore worth of idle money. bd
